        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-10-31 16:17:27.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI made quite a few comments about ordering fields, I think most of the classes in 1.3 followed:\n\nname (always there)\ntype (often there)\nuuid (always there)\nmodelInvariantUUID (often there)\nmodelVersionID (new to 1.4 but there in a lot of cases)\n:\nanyOtherClassSpeficFields (depends)\n:\ndataQuality\nattributeList\n\nWe don't have to keep with this scheme if there is something that makes more sense architecturally, but I think we should be consistent.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "9aed96144d2150102d7972ac4637b1137b1a095b",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3131,
